#. <section class="sutta" id="sn56.46"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn56.46:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 56"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 56"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.46:0.2"
msgid "5. Papātavagga"
msgstr "5. A Cliff"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn56.46:0.3"
msgid "46. Andhakārasutta"
msgstr "46. Darkness"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.46:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Atthi, bhikkhave, lokantarikā aghā asaṃvutā andhakārā andhakāratimisā, "
"yatthamimesaṃ candimasūriyānaṃ evaṃmahiddhikānaṃ evaṃ mahānubhāvānaṃ ābhāya "
"nānubhontī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, the boundless desolation of interstellar space is so utterly "
"dark that even the light of the moon and the sun, so mighty and powerful, "
"makes no impression.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.46:2.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, aññataro bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, one of the mendicants asked the Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn56.46:2.2"
msgid "“mahā vata so, bhante, andhakāro, sumahā vata so, bhante, andhakāro."
msgstr "“Sir, that darkness really is intense, so very intense."

msgctxt "sn56.46:2.3"
msgid ""
"Atthi nu kho, bhante, etamhā andhakārā añño andhakāro mahantataro ca "
"bhayānakataro cā”ti?"
msgstr "Is there any other darkness more intense and scarier than this one?”"

msgctxt "sn56.46:2.4"
msgid ""
"“Atthi kho, bhikkhu, etamhā andhakārā añño andhakāro mahantataro ca "
"bhayānakataro cā”ti."
msgstr "“There is, mendicant.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.455"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.46:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Katamo pana, bhante, etamhā andhakārā añño andhakāro mahantataro ca "
"bhayānakataro cā”ti?"
msgstr "“But sir, what is it?”"

msgctxt "sn56.46:3.2"
msgid ""
"“Ye hi keci, bhikkhu, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ "
"nappajānanti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ "
"nappajānanti,"
msgstr ""
"“There are ascetics and brahmins who don’t truly understand about suffering, "
"its origin, its cessation, and the path."

msgctxt "sn56.46:3.3"
msgid "te jātisaṃvattanikesu saṅkhāresu abhiramanti … pe …"
msgstr "They take pleasure in choices that lead to rebirth …"

msgctxt "sn56.46:3.4"
msgid "abhiratā … pe … abhisaṅkharonti … pe …"
msgstr "They continue to make such choices …"

msgctxt "sn56.46:3.5"
msgid ""
"abhisaṅkharitvā jātandhakārampi papatanti, jarandhakārampi papatanti, "
"maraṇandhakārampi papatanti, sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsandhakārampi "
"papatanti."
msgstr ""
"Having made such choices, they fall into the darkness of rebirth, old age, "
"and death, of sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress."

msgctxt "sn56.46:3.6"
msgid ""
"Te na parimuccanti jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi "
"domanassehi upāyāsehi."
msgstr ""
"They’re not freed from rebirth, old age, and death, from sorrow, "
"lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress."

msgctxt "sn56.46:3.7"
msgid "‘Na parimuccanti dukkhasmā’ti vadāmi."
msgstr "They’re not freed from suffering, I say."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.46:4.1"
msgid ""
"Ye ca kho keci, bhikkhu, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ "
"pajānanti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānanti,"
msgstr ""
"There are ascetics and brahmins who truly understand about suffering, its "
"origin, its cessation, and the path."

msgctxt "sn56.46:4.2"
msgid "te jātisaṃvattanikesu saṅkhāresu nābhiramanti … pe …"
msgstr "They don’t take pleasure in choices that lead to rebirth …"

msgctxt "sn56.46:4.3"
msgid "anabhiratā … pe … nābhisaṅkharonti … pe …"
msgstr "They stop making such choices …"

msgctxt "sn56.46:4.4"
msgid ""
"anabhisaṅkharitvā jātandhakārampi nappapatanti, jarandhakārampi "
"nappapatanti, maraṇandhakārampi nappapatanti, "
"sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsandhakārampi nappapatanti."
msgstr ""
"Having stopped making such choices, they don’t fall into the darkness of "
"rebirth, old age, and death, of sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and "
"distress."

msgctxt "sn56.46:4.5"
msgid ""
"Te parimuccanti jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi "
"domanassehi upāyāsehi."
msgstr ""
"They’re freed from rebirth, old age, and death, from sorrow, lamentation, "
"pain, sadness, and distress."

msgctxt "sn56.46:4.6"
msgid "‘Parimuccanti dukkhasmā’ti vadāmi."
msgstr "They’re freed from suffering, I say."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.46:5.1"
msgid ""
"Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yogo karaṇīyo … pe … ‘ayaṃ "
"dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yogo karaṇīyo”ti."
msgstr "That’s why you should practice meditation …”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.46:5.2"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
